1
00:00:01,540 --> 00:00:02,729
Excuse me.

2
00:00:02,730 --> 00:00:06,680
The interviewer was the older guy
who hit on you. That's just insane.

3
00:00:06,940 --> 00:00:08,680
I really look like a kid, don't I?

4
00:00:09,320 --> 00:00:11,380
Making people worry and
needing to be comforted.

5
00:00:13,020 --> 00:00:14,880
- Excuse me.
- Ai-chan.

6
00:00:15,500 --> 00:00:20,900
This guy is a real catch.
Please take good care of him.

7
00:00:21,360 --> 00:00:24,400
He likes you, doesn't he?

8
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:27,620
I won't join Okumi-san's company.

9
00:00:28,020 --> 00:00:30,320
So please reject my application.

10
00:00:30,860 --> 00:00:32,179
I got the job offer.

11
00:00:32,180 --> 00:00:33,640
- Huh?
- How did that happen?

12
00:00:53,060 --> 00:00:55,140
He's just too cute.

13
00:00:57,520 --> 00:01:00,420
Even though he's a cute boy,

14
00:01:02,860 --> 00:01:05,200
he shouldn't be looking at dating sites
so openly.

15
00:01:08,740 --> 00:01:09,740
Hmm?

16
00:01:26,020 --> 00:01:28,300
You don't look so well.
Are you okay?

17
00:01:44,560 --> 00:01:47,000
From the very beginning, I...

18
00:01:48,940 --> 00:01:52,540
I never thought I'd fall in
love at first sight at this age.

19
00:01:54,300 --> 00:01:56,219
That cake from last time was so good.

20
00:01:56,220 --> 00:01:58,139
- It really was.
- I want to go again.

21
00:01:58,140 --> 00:01:59,176
- You want to go again?
- Yeah.

22
00:01:59,200 --> 00:02:00,200
Let's go next week.

23
00:02:00,920 --> 00:02:02,360
So young.

24
00:02:12,090 --> 00:02:15,160
"Are the Sexy Buttocks Not Good?"

25
00:02:15,800 --> 00:02:19,300
(Episode 3)

26
00:02:19,340 --> 00:02:21,340
You got a job offer from
that older guy's company?

27
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:25,160
But I didn't know he was the president
until the final interview.

28
00:02:26,360 --> 00:02:27,579
I got the job offer.

29
00:02:27,580 --> 00:02:29,559
- Huh?
- How did that happen?

30
00:02:29,560 --> 00:02:32,740
Hiring in our company
is decided by the HR department.

31
00:02:35,100 --> 00:02:36,100
Are you serious?

32
00:02:36,640 --> 00:02:38,139
So what are you going to do?

33
00:02:38,140 --> 00:02:39,160
Are you going to take it?

34
00:02:41,060 --> 00:02:42,260
I am.

35
00:02:44,346 --> 00:02:45,766
The president, huh...

36
00:02:48,560 --> 00:02:51,030
(Words from my late wife)

37
00:02:54,500 --> 00:02:55,500
What's wrong?

38
00:02:57,320 --> 00:02:58,320
Nothing.

39
00:02:58,680 --> 00:02:59,680
It's nothing.

40
00:03:01,540 --> 00:03:02,540
Come on, what is it?

41
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:04,880
No, really, it's nothing.

42
00:03:06,280 --> 00:03:07,620
- Let me see.
- Ah.

43
00:03:11,720 --> 00:03:16,120
(Words from my late wife)

44
00:03:17,040 --> 00:03:18,040
See?

45
00:03:18,520 --> 00:03:22,120
Just because he was married
doesn't mean he only likes women.

46
00:03:22,820 --> 00:03:25,160
Plus, it confirms he's single.
Isn't that a good thing?

47
00:03:26,820 --> 00:03:29,100
I don't even know if he likes me.

48
00:03:31,760 --> 00:03:34,740
(Maybe he actually prefers women.)

49
00:03:36,773 --> 00:03:38,552
Why don't you just ask him directly?

50
00:03:38,880 --> 00:03:39,880
No way.

51
00:03:39,900 --> 00:03:41,700
Asking something like
that feels so childish.

52
00:03:52,840 --> 00:03:56,020
(He was married, right?)

53
00:03:58,400 --> 00:04:02,620
(A divorced older guy
with someone so young...)

54
00:04:05,080 --> 00:04:07,740
(If he really likes women...)

55
00:04:09,033 --> 00:04:11,613
(Things are great now,
but what about later?)

56
00:04:13,720 --> 00:04:16,339
(What if he doesn't
actually like me that much?)

57
00:04:18,720 --> 00:04:22,420
(He might not always like me.)

58
00:04:35,260 --> 00:04:36,260
Wait.

59
00:04:36,320 --> 00:04:37,880
- We're outside.
- Sorry.

60
00:04:39,020 --> 00:04:40,100
You're just too cute.

61
00:04:44,280 --> 00:04:48,940
(I thought you were adorable the first time
we met. I couldn't bear to let you go.)

62
00:05:03,300 --> 00:05:04,360
Come in.

63
00:05:06,560 --> 00:05:08,460
Excuse me.

64
00:05:11,820 --> 00:05:12,820
It's so spacious.

65
00:05:25,220 --> 00:05:26,620
It's been a while, Ai-chan.

66
00:05:27,240 --> 00:05:28,780
It's only been a week.

67
00:05:29,080 --> 00:05:31,140
You should praise me
for holding back until now.

68
00:05:31,740 --> 00:05:34,120
Stop joking around, old man.

69
00:05:41,220 --> 00:05:42,619
- Come here.
- No, no.

70
00:05:42,620 --> 00:05:47,700
(But an older guy's true feelings must be
a burden for someone as young as you.)

71
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:51,990
(Even so, right now...)

72
00:06:04,520 --> 00:06:06,000
Are you busy, Mr. President?

73
00:06:06,200 --> 00:06:08,720
Huh? Well, I wouldn't say
I have a lot of free time.

74
00:06:09,200 --> 00:06:10,220
What's wrong?

75
00:06:10,620 --> 00:06:12,920
Doing this takes a lot of energy.

76
00:06:13,540 --> 00:06:15,060
I was wondering if you'd be too tired.

77
00:06:17,580 --> 00:06:18,580
Then,

78
00:06:18,813 --> 00:06:22,813
Can I get a reward
for working so hard just to see you?

79
00:06:34,420 --> 00:06:35,420
Ah.

80
00:06:36,360 --> 00:06:37,800
What kind of reward?

81
00:06:39,540 --> 00:06:42,940
Let me see more of your face
when you feel good, Ai-chan.

82
00:06:47,460 --> 00:06:48,460
Ah.

83
00:06:59,280 --> 00:07:01,680
You actually have a mole here.

84
00:07:06,140 --> 00:07:07,200
Ah.

85
00:07:10,120 --> 00:07:13,420
Probably only my parents know about that.

86
00:07:19,833 --> 00:07:24,833
Then you absolutely can't
let anyone else see it.

87
00:07:48,440 --> 00:07:50,080
What do you like about me?

88
00:07:52,380 --> 00:07:54,380
Am I not showing you enough love?

89
00:07:54,580 --> 00:07:56,040
It's more than enough.

90
00:07:57,940 --> 00:07:58,940
It's just that,

91
00:07:59,740 --> 00:08:02,360
I sometimes wonder if I'm
really good enough for you.

92
00:08:06,220 --> 00:08:07,220
Ai-chan.

93
00:08:08,420 --> 00:08:09,420
You know,

94
00:08:10,080 --> 00:08:13,860
- I was actually married once.
- Yeah.

95
00:08:15,080 --> 00:08:16,700
Huh, you don't seem very surprised.

96
00:08:17,840 --> 00:08:20,300
I read an interview online.

97
00:08:22,820 --> 00:08:24,940
Right. I am a second-generation
successor, after all.

98
00:08:25,120 --> 00:08:28,076
Back then, I didn't have the luxury
to figure out if I was gay or bisexual.

99
00:08:28,100 --> 00:08:30,060
I didn't have anyone I
liked at the time, either.

100
00:08:30,280 --> 00:08:32,700
I just thought that was
how life was supposed to be.

101
00:08:34,800 --> 00:08:38,919
Fortunately, she was a good person.
As we lived together, gradually,

102
00:08:38,920 --> 00:08:41,540
we developed feelings similar to love.

103
00:08:43,940 --> 00:08:45,300
Then she got sick.

104
00:08:51,360 --> 00:08:52,940
She passed away very suddenly.

105
00:08:58,040 --> 00:09:02,199
So I thought I'd never fall in love again
and just die alone.

106
00:09:02,240 --> 00:09:03,670
I never expected

107
00:09:03,820 --> 00:09:05,440
that I would meet you.

108
00:09:10,320 --> 00:09:11,520
Ah, sorry.

109
00:09:12,100 --> 00:09:13,540
That got too heavy.

110
00:09:13,620 --> 00:09:14,660
I'll go change the sheets.

111
00:09:31,880 --> 00:09:34,380
(How could I put him in a tough spot?)

112
00:09:37,200 --> 00:09:40,420
(I really didn't want him
to make that kind of face.)

113
00:09:50,380 --> 00:09:51,420
Ai-chan.

114
00:09:57,620 --> 00:09:58,620
Lone...

115
00:10:00,520 --> 00:10:01,540
Lone?

116
00:10:03,740 --> 00:10:07,240
If you're lonely, I'm still here.

117
00:10:17,700 --> 00:10:18,700
Listen,

118
00:10:20,700 --> 00:10:25,700
Can we cancel the promise
about dating until you get bored of me?

119
00:10:29,320 --> 00:10:30,520
I want to be with you forever.

120
00:10:32,960 --> 00:10:34,720
Not just until I get bored.

121
00:10:35,640 --> 00:10:39,040
I'd cry if you ever got bored of me.

122
00:10:41,160 --> 00:10:42,160
Give me a break.

123
00:10:43,140 --> 00:10:45,700
You'd dump me without hesitation
if you got bored, wouldn't you?

124
00:10:47,500 --> 00:10:48,800
That's impossible.

125
00:10:53,680 --> 00:10:54,680
Is that a no?

126
00:11:00,040 --> 00:11:03,400
Whether it's nursing care or whatever, I'll
take care of you for the rest of my life.

127
00:11:06,760 --> 00:11:10,280
I'll do everything I can
to extend my healthy lifespan.

128
00:11:21,120 --> 00:11:22,180
Okumi-san.

129
00:11:26,020 --> 00:11:27,020
Ai-chan.

130
00:11:27,840 --> 00:11:29,700
Can we do it one more time?

131
00:11:46,740 --> 00:11:47,759
Hmm?

132
00:11:47,760 --> 00:11:49,019
I already took a shower.

133
00:11:49,020 --> 00:11:50,219
A shower?

134
00:11:50,220 --> 00:11:51,480
We can just take another one.

135
00:12:45,300 --> 00:12:48,060
(Next Episode) This is my
first time having an office romance.

136
00:12:48,340 --> 00:12:51,500
You're starting to want to be happy.
Isn't that a good thing?

137
00:12:51,900 --> 00:12:52,346
Ah!

138
00:12:52,410 --> 00:12:55,916
I'm completely useless at the
company. Why did they even hire me?

139
00:12:55,940 --> 00:12:59,460
If you feel bad about it,
then make it up to me.

